Brazilian Stock Movers: ALL America Latina, Kroton, Mundial

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-07-22T20:19:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/brazilian-stock-movers-all-america-latina-kroton-mundial.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index was little changed at 60,270.47.  ALL America Latina Logistica SA (ALLL3)  (ALLL3 BS) rose 1.2 percent
to 12.23 reais.  Latin America ’s largest railroad company said
total volume transported rose 8.9 percent in the second quarter
from a year earlier. Earnings before interest, taxes,
depreciation and amortization rose 12.2 percent, ALL said in a
regulatory filing. The results are preliminary.  Kroton Educacional SA (KROT11 BS), an administrator of
private schools and colleges, slipped 0.9 percent to 19.05
reais. Kroton peer Abril Educacao SA, an education and
publishing group, sold shares below the projected range in an
initial public offering.  Mundial SA Produtos de Consumo (MNDL4 BS) plunged 64
percent to 69 centavos. The Brazilian consumer-goods maker fell
for a third day, for a combined loss of 86 percent, amid
speculation that recent gains had been excessive given the
company’s growth outlook.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in  Sao Paulo  at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
